It was a long drive, but the excitement of playing in the sand and splashing in the water kept me super hyped the whole way there. When we finally arrived, I ran towards the ocean, feeling the salty breeze and hearing the seagulls squawking—it was pure joy. I spent the whole day building sandcastles and collecting seashells with my siblings. As the sun set, we sat around a bonfire, roasting marshmallows and sharing stories. It was just one of those perfect days that sticks with you, you know?
